comments: This was a difficult but fun study!

The game was intriguing meaning. I love it
Cool study, I liked it a lot. More like this please!

Wish I could have the solution on the games I couldn't beat.
No issues encountered, it was a fun and worthwhile study

I usually play puzzle games, but these were a challenge, though I definitely feel like with more time I would've figured them out! Thanks for the challenge and survey!  P.S. Found the link to the puzzles, thank you!

Thank you for the break, enjoy your day!

Thanks so much. The only annoyance was not being able to solve the puzzles!

some of the puzzles felt like they were impossible to solve.

I felt like most of these weren't actually solvable (I don't really play this genre so am probably wrong)
No problems noted, I did like the challenge of the games although I think a couple of them had no solution :)

Was that last puzzle really solvable?

it feels so new to me but interesting

The puzzles reminded me of Pokemon, when players use the HM Strength with their Pokemon in caves to push boulders around into holes! I think there may have also been a gym puzzle that was similar to this in one of the games too.
How cruel, once I finally get the solution, you don't let me complete the puzzle by pushing that last square into the blue.

After a few puzzles I had to change my screen size because the surveys/questions wouldn't scroll down to show the submit button. Other than that, I had a ton of fun trying to figure these out! Thank you!

interesting and very educative. I really force me to think and apply different strategy in solving the puzzle

I have never played this type of game. I found the game very challenging.

Everything was pretty clear and I did not experience any technical issues. I was getting a bit frustrated not being able to replicate what I accomplished prior to the break. If I had a little more time I think I could have got back on track and solved it.
I don't think all of these were possible to solve but maybe that's the point
I enjoyed the puzzles, especially when I had a difficult puzzle and then was able to come back after the break, and figure it out.
